parameters.name: domainIdentifier
parameters.description: The ID of the Amazon DataZone domain where you want to list metadata generation runs.

nested_items.name: items
nested_items.description: The results of the ListMetadataGenerationRuns action.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The timestamp at which the metadata generation run was created.

nested_items.name: createdBy
nested_items.description: The user who created the metadata generation run.

nested_items.name: domainId
nested_items.description: The ID of the Amazon DataZone domain in which the metadata generation run was created.

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: The ID of the metadata generation run.

nested_items.name: owningProjectId
nested_items.description: The ID of the project that owns the asset for which the metadata generation was ran.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status of the metadata generation run.

nested_items.name: identifier
nested_items.description: The ID of the metadata generation run's target.

nested_items.name: revision
nested_items.description: The revision of the asset for which metadata was generated.

nested_items.name: type
nested_items.description: The type of the asset for which metadata was generated.

nested_items.name: type
nested_items.description: The type of the metadata generation run.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: When the number of metadata generation runs is greater than the default value for the MaxResults parameter, or if you explicitly specify a value for MaxResults that is less than the number of metadata generation runs, the response includes a pagination token named NextToken. You can specify this NextToken value in a subsequent call to ListMetadataGenerationRuns to list the next set of revisions.
